<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, ends on Em (Aeolian). Modal feel with chromatic passing chords (Eb, Bb).
- LH: Em E2-B2-E3-G3; G: G2-D3-G3-B3; D: D2-A2-D3-F#3; Am: A2-E3-A3-C4.
- Eb passing chords (bars 1, 4 and 6, 7) treated as IV-Lydian color (scale degree 4b).
- RH: light 2-note thirds, stepping with melody.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Chromatic voice F#→F in bars 1 and 7 creates distinctive modal descent.
- Bars 5-6: D7-C-G progression with clear bass motion D2-C2-G2.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup: sparse single note lead-in
- Bars 1-4: moderate, modal opening
- Bars 5-7: chromatic intensification
- Bar 8: Em resolution, final cadence
-->
